project_name: UPM-G99 Generator Export to Grid Protection New Requirement
status_history: here is the status change history of project in numbering order(1):work in progress by Jayme Feil

scope_of_work.notes:
1. Does not include any client contingency 
2. Assumes that CBRE hold the burden of the actual cost whether it is over or under the quotation value 
3. Maintenance contract budget variations as a result of project activity will be funded by client through the eBVO process
scope_of_work.problem: There is a new DNO electricity supply requirement named G99 with revised limits of export power from site generators to the national grid. Those sites and systems must adhere and operate within the new requirements and install new hardware as required and to test the systems with DNO witnessing
scope_of_work.scope: Install new hardware to the 3 Kyndryl Warwick systems, IRS, Ph1 and Ph1A. Complete comprehensive soft transfer tests of switchboards from Mains to Generators. On completion of testing with specialist, demonstrate to the DNO compliance of each system to the new G99 requirements
scope_of_work.justification: Soft, closed transition or no break transfers as they are known enables Kyndryl to test their generators and LV ACB automatic operation on a monthly basis. This minimises the risk of generator or circuit breaker component failure when they are called upon to operate in a Mains Fail situation
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Loss of transfer facility with no breaks and the flexibility the system provides if there is a need to transfer. Increased risk of business load loss as UPS load can and has transferred to Raw Mains supply via static switches for a UPS or LV Switchboard major fault. The Raw switchboard will not be able to transfer to generator supply and the load will remain on Mains utility until the UPS or switchboard failure is resolved

scope_of_work.problem: It is the manufacturers recommendation that the East Powerhouse ACB's are maintained as they are 5 years old
scope_of_work.scope:
Attend CBRE office for induction and sign relevant paperwork
All switching to be completed by CBRE
Handover ACB to contractor to carry out maintenace as follows
Air Circuit Breakers
- Full 20 Point mechanical service.
- All Coils / Accessories functionality and impedance checked – where possible.
- Moving / Arcing contacts cleaned / inspected. Contact wear and arcing contact gaps measured
and recorded.
- Protection Release injected at multiple thresholds. All trip times verified against manufacturer’s
tripping curves.
- 30 Mechanical service operations carried out.
- Fixed Portion cleaned and subject to 10 Point inspection.
- Mechanical interlock visually inspected for set up and functionality.
- ACB low Ohm continuity (10A) and insulation resistance (500v) tested.
- Successful re-instatement.
Restore ACB to normal service
Sign off relevant paperwork
scope_of_work.justification: It is the manufacturers recommendation that the East Powerhouse ACB's are maintained as they are 5 years old. Maintenance can reduce the risk of failure of parts resulting in possible outage on the UPS system which will in turn affect the IT load
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Maintenance can reduce the risk of failure of parts resulting in possible outage on the UPS system which will in turn affect the IT load

scope_of_work.problem: Following the removal of the Spare SF6 HV CB due to gas loss, it was found that there was tracking on the Busbar. It is recommended that the Inspection and Testing of the bus bar chamber. Bus bar, intermediate & end fittings is carried out
scope_of_work.scope: Attend CBRE office and sign relevant paperwork. Freedom operatives will remove all covers from the bus bar chamber. Bus bar, intermediate & end fittings will be inspected, with their condition recorded. All connections will be checked ensuring they’re to the correct torque setting as per the manufacturer’s instructions, finally a conductor test will be carried out using a low resistance ohmmeter
scope_of_work.justification: High voltage fault on the system could lead to significant failure of the HV supply to site and in worst cases. fire leading to damage to site electrical infrastructure.
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Failure of the electrical infrastructure to site and potential of fire damage.
